<p><font color="#000000" size="4">These two features of .NET, web
services and assembly version provide it with a great deal of
power to offer many useful services and benefits to both
developers and businesses.</font></p>

<ul>
    <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Reusable web-services</font><ul>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Web services are
                able to be written in the language best suited to
                carrying out the job</font></li>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Any programmer can
                debug web-service calls across service and
                component boundaries without requiring
                familiarity with the language in which the
                service or component was written</font></li>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Reduces cost</font></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Multi-platform</font><ul>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">.NET and web
                services may be run on Windows, Unix, PalmOS</font></li>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">XML is the common
                exchange medium</font></li>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">SOAP as common RPC
                protocol</font></li>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Open standards!</font></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Device compatibility</font><ul>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Web services can
                work with any device, without requiring
                specialized device drivers for interacting with
                it</font></li>
            <li><font color="#000000" size="4">Simplified service
                interface leads to simplified development and
                reduced cost</font></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

